JS Temporal PlainDateTime:

- A Temporal.PlainDateTime represents a date and time without a time zone.


#) Create a PlainDateTime
    - 1ï¸âƒ£ You can create a PlainDateTime from a string.
            const dateTime = Temporal.PlainDateTime.from("2026-05-17T10:00:00");    // 2026-05-17T10:00:00
    
    - 2ï¸âƒ£ You can also create one using numeric values.
            const dateTime = new Temporal.PlainDateTime(2026, 5, 17, 10, 0);    // 2026-05-17T10:00:00


#) Get the Current Date and Time:
    - Use Temporal.Now.plainDateTimeISO() to get the current date and time.
            const now = Temporal.Now.plainDateTimeISO();    // 2026-02-25T20:27:22.013469971


#) Temporal.PlainTime();
    - âš ï¸ The Temporal PlainTime() method creates a time object with no date.
    - It returns an ISO 8601 wall-clock time without a date or time zone.
            const date = new Temporal.PlainTime(10, 30);    // 10:30:00


#) Add or Subtract Time:
    - You can safely add or subtract time.
    -ğŸ’¡The original value does not change.

            const dateTime = Temporal.PlainDateTime.from("2026-05-17T10:00:00");    // 2026-05-17T10:00:00 
            const earlier = dateTime.subtract({ minutes: 30 });                     // 2026-05-17T09:30:00
            const later = dateTime.add({ hours: 2 });                               // 2026-05-17T12:00:00


#) Compare PlainDateTime Values:
    - ğŸ’¡You can use equals().
            const a = Temporal.PlainDateTime.from("2026-05-17T10:00:00");
            const b = Temporal.PlainDateTime.from("2026-05-17T10:00:00");

            document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = a.equals(b);    // true


#) Convert to ZonedDateTime:
    - As we know now, a PlainDateTime does not include time zone information.
    - ğŸ’¡ but You can convert it to a ZonedDateTime if needed.
            const dateTime = Temporal.PlainDateTime.from("2026-05-17T10:00:00");    // 2026-05-17T10:00:00
            const zoned = dateTime.toZonedDateTime("Asia/Kathmandu");   // 2026-05-17T10:00:00+05:45[Asia/Kathmandu]


#) When to Use PlainDateTime:
    ğŸ‘‰ Local event scheduling.
    ğŸ‘‰ Appointments without international time zone handling.
    ğŸ‘‰ Forms that collect date and time.
    ğŸ‘‰ Applications where time zone conversion is not required.